<br>
Secondly however, though it may seem as you did not get to go because someone of higher level just decided to show up, fact is I was asked to come to the raid approximately a month ago.  Before it was even posted I believe.  I do know that what you speak of did infact happen for some people, but rest assured that you did not get bumped because a higher level SK just happened to pop his head into SRo this morning.<br>
<br>
Also, you need to keep in mind that this wasn't just your average pick-up/loot Hate raid, where you clear as many mobs as you can on the first floor then leave.  The object was to take out as many of the mini-bosses as possible for epic drops and whatnot, then move on to the second floor where the mobs are much much tougher (imo they're all almost mini-bosses in their own right, I have the battlescars to prove it as I was the only puller on the second floor =p).  So yes level would obviously be a big factor in choosing who gets to attend.<br>
<br>
As far as Siilv showing up late goes, she's only human, she made a mistake.  Oops.  I spent that time keeping a little level 12 warrior alive at the Derv camp with my pathetic little dark empathy heals heh.  He was happy as hell <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   What did you do during that time besides sending me tells complaining about the loot rules and whatnot?  I found something constructive to do and hopefully made someones day.  If for some reason I was not chosen to go later I would have shrugged it off and found something else to do.  Wouldn't be the first time I planned on going to a plane and ended up not going, and I'm sure it won't be the last.  A few times due to my level too.  That's just the way it goes with pickup raids sometimes.  Which come to think of it this didn't really classify as, it was actually 2 guilds hosting it and coming here to fill in some needed spots.  Not a pure pickup raid.  <br>
<br>
So, sorry to see you get your panties in a bunch over it but hey, least you got to watch the superbowl today if you wanted to.  I was watching All Hail Innoruuk spammed across my screen every few minutes until we finally killed that damned Evangelist :P  Also, if it makes you feel any better, out of the 7 or 8 Drakes we killed not one decrepit hide dropped.  In fact, I think only one thing that was SK usable dropped all day and a stinky Paladin won it (nasty do-gooders!), so you didn't miss out on a whole lot.  All I can say is level up and increase your chances of making the cut next time.  Good luck to you mano.<br>
